TopicTitle: [Music] - Classic-Electronic...but what to classify it as?

Articles.Content:
Tried something a bit different, but not sure what genre it would be considered.

https://soundcloud.com/billy-winn-2/from-dust

Take a listen and let me know what you would consider it. Keep it mind it changes up a bit after the intro

Like it. Somewhere between Jean Michel Jarre and VNV Nation.

"Minimalist Electronic", perhaps?

No, can't be minimalist. Also I don't see where's the classical part. Just because there are violines doesn't mean it's classical.

This is similar to some soundtracks we hear in blockbuster movies. I can't pinpoint it down on the genre spectrum.
